makers, as well as those individuals interested in EU law, in the intricacies of consumer protection, contractual law, timesharing, and other important aspects in the harmonization of domestic and EU law books. The detailed analysis and research this volume accomplishes is invaluable to those scholars and lawmakers who are the next generation of European leaders.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jul 2022) 0aCommercial lawxEuropean Union countries. 0aCommercial lawzEuropean Union countries. 0aConsumer protectionxEuropean Union countries. 0aConsumer protectionzEuropean Union countries. 0aContractsxEuropean Union countries. 0aContractszEuropean Union countries. 0aProducts liabilityxEuropean Union countries. 0aProducts liabilityzEuropean Union countries. 0aRestraint of tradexEuropean Union countries. 0aRestraint of tradezEuropean Union countries. 7aLAW / Civil Law.2bisacsh  aCommercial law, Consumer protection, Contracts, Economic integration, European Union, Integration.1 aPasa, Barbara, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertCentral European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998z978311078055040uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978615505382540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9786155053825423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9786155053825/original  a978-3-11-078055-0  Central European University Press eBook-Package 2013-1998c1998d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_LAEC  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LAEC  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_ESTMALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA18STMEE  aPDA5EBK